In other matters wee ſhew an active agility, in this only a ſenſeles and dull ſtupidity which that God Almighty may correct and amend in us, he ſends us to the Ant, an example of Induſtry and diligence;
Prov. 6. 
               Go to the Ant thou ſtuggard, Behould her wayes and be wiſe. She by the very guidance and Inſtinct of Nature, knowing that food is not to be got in Winter, gathers her food in Harveſt and prepares her meat in Summer.

Woe unto you rich men, for you have your Conſolation;

   Luk. 6. Luk. 8. 
Woe unto you that be full becauſe ye ſhall hunger, Woe unto you that laugh now, becauſe ye ſhall mourne and weep. Againe we find it recorded in St. Luke.
